    notes: "Aggregate=3567 | easy_ft06=55 | hard_ft20=1165 | medium_ft10=930 | very_hard_swv01=1417 | This approach enhances the MILP formulation by incorporating CP-SAT derived feasibility cuts. After obtaining a warm-start solution from CP-SAT, we analyze the scheduling decisions made by the CP solver and add nogood cuts to the MILP model. These cuts help guide the MILP solver away from infeasible regions of the solution space that the CP solver already explored, potentially leading to faster convergence and better solutions. The algorithm maintains the original MILP structure with tight big-M constants and precedence cuts while adding these new feasibility constraints."
